pageContext.claim: “Our unemployment rate, real unemployment, 3.6, 3.7 -- and going down, had a little blip because of a thing called the shutdown. But remember, it went up to 4.0. I said, "Boy, that's -- " Do you know how low 4.0 is? Do you know anybody else, any other president that would have said, 'Please give me 4.0, please?'”
pageContext.analysis: Since World War II, the unemployment rate was 4.0 or below in the presidencies of Bill Clinton, Richard Nixon, Lyndon Johnson, Dwight Eisenhower and Harry Truman.
